<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12664] GCCompactionTest is flaky</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12664</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;GCCompactionTest&lt;/tt&gt; was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7019&quot; title=&quot;Improve tombstone compactions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7019&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7019&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and appears to be flaky, see for example &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/sbtourist/job/sbtourist-CASSANDRA-9318-trunk-testall/lastCompletedBuild/testReport/org.apache.cassandra.cql3/GcCompactionTest/testGcCompactionStatic/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s the same root cause as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12282&quot; title=&quot;SSTablesIteratedTest.testDeletionOnIndexedSSTableASC-compression failure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-12282&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-12282&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: the tables in the test keyspace are dropped asynchronously after each test, and this might cause additional flush operations for all dirty tables in the keyspace. See the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12282?focusedCommentId=15399098&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15399098&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;callstack&lt;/a&gt; in 12282. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A possible solution is to use KEYSPACE_PER_TEST, which is instead dropped synchronously.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
